If there was one thing you could learn that would change your life forever, just one thing... what would it be and why?
Adam Taha
Into developing leaders · Author has 5K answers and 94.5M answer views · 7y ·

“It is not what you need but what you already got that will take you as far as you want to go…”

This is my philosphy that has changed my life and the life of people around the world. I know it may seem difficult because…

  • You might have no money
  • You might have no tools
  • AND you might be in a situation no one believes in you. Not even you’re cat or dog that looks up to you and thinks, “you’re a loser.”

When you don’t worry about what what you got and use what you need, then you learn to become resourceful.

You can adapt fast and become very creative to solve problems.

The challenge is a lot of people won’t have the patience for this because they want money now, they want results now and sometimes, that one thing can take you a long time to get done because…..you’re starting from what you got.

And what you got can be a challenge as you don’t have money and other resources.

But what if when you just take action and persist, with clear mind what you are going to achieve, that other things will come your way?

Here’s some examples, a blast from the past…

1. Use What You Already Got…
I do things because they make me feel alive. I don’t look for passion but love what I do. Passion then comes anyway.

So with this thought….I had an idea for a Magazine.

But what will it do?

I saw a problem in community and so I investigated and found in the city, many organisations, funders, and talents but no one is talking to each other. Confusion, lack of communication, no channel for all to look to.

People didn’t know where to go for help, information, advise and no one really knew what or who was doing what.

But I got no computer?

I knew some places like centres and colleges.

I went to them one by one until one said, “ok, come and use ours.”

You’ll find people who value what you value if you just keep looking and put time into. Made pals with some folks there and they let me use the computer if I will share techie skills. I would walk for 2 hours there to do my work and 2 hours back to design layout, ready for the content..

I rummaged through some stuff and found relatives had a camera. So..I nicked it! Hahaha. No one was using it. I thought if I use it fast to do work and bring it back all will be well.

I began going to go all over city, talking photos, talking to businesses, interviewing them and talents, and funders.

Word was getting round that some guy is creating a magazine but you know how it is with talk. No one believes you until it’s done.

I wrote the magazine, designing and printed copies from a shit printer, stapled it together and went to these business and pitched how funders will give them more money, if they show they investing in community and…it be seen THEY lead the way not me. So they will look good.

They were in!

I got money for printing and distribution.

Magazine was giving out free so each business who advertised got copies to give to people, funders too and I put some in different shops for people to take. I paid the printers.

Printed 8,000 copies and got it distributed and this attracted funders to pay for more issues until I gave the project to someone else to do.

I did wanted and in return…a business man bought me the lastest Laptop and other gear. So I was off to doing another idea I picked from my list.

2. When You Want A Job and Change Of Career…
So on the line of giving, there was this guy who bought a franchise business. It wasn’t going well at all. His heart wasn’t in it. He always wanted to be this guy who creates his own stuff and be a marketer.

He liked digital.

His business going bankcrupt. His girlfriend leaving him. He’s losing the house. He’s seriously in trouble.

I didn’t know how to build websites and all that stuff. All I knew is marketing and the knowledge in my head that works in the real world..

He took my advise to move into his parents house and take the headache they give for a while. In 6 months he’ll get the job he wants and wage he wants. He also has let go of his cat but promised his cat, he will come back for him.

Research started in the industry and narrowing it down to a specific job title….digital marketing manager. We now knew their lingo, what they look for, what they didn’t look for, what turns them on. Great for lazer targeting for later.

We had back and forth skype conversation, providing him direction for knowledge on marketing, sales, social media marketing, and he learnt Facebook Advertising/PPC.

He got an idea now of a strategy and a marketing plan…

I transfered lots of my knowledge and skill to him regarding copywriting and design, science of storytelling, psychology etc cetre.

The guy was one brave guy. He put the hard work in, the belief and just went on to do what is necessary. He proved to me he was deadly serious.

He wasn’t talk.

He got his website built….

I know it’s not some fancy website.

It’s not amazing design but hey, just forget about that for now.

The idea was to show his intiative, his skills, his knowledge by building his own website, showing copywriting skills and all the skills companies he wants to work with…look for. To create a track record.

I even got him some clients to do work for so he can show the work on his website and his CV. Even though it was attracting the companies, we made sure not to be afraid in the protocol on contacting him…i.e. what he is looking for and what he is not clearly on the website.

No ass kissing. Nothing like trying to lower his standards. None of that.

When all was done…he did the facebook advertising and used Twitter too. Some people were like “but this is an old retro design..”

However, the result…...he got the interviews and the job.

He’s now a Digital Marketing Manager for a blue chip company that specialises marketing with mobile phones and other digital devises.

He’s doing what he loves to do and find his own place, a home to move into. He also bought his cat back :D

3. When You’re Degree Is Not Enough
The same process and philosphy I applied to a woman who needed help. She finished her degree but she just couldn’t get a job in product design and any job.

She needed help because she was in debt with student loan, she was confused where her future now is going.

So again, the same process I did with Johnny, I did with her too. This time, I now had a team of web developer professionals willing to work with me to help people. We got the money, she was willing to invest because she seen what can be done and she was teachable, coachable and ready to go for it.

She is now working as well in a job and getting interest from companies to be a product designer…

Here’s her video. Let her tell her own story how it happened…

4. When You Haven’t Got Money and Website
Right now, the world is telling you what you need. You need a website. You need this and you need that. You need to be in facebook, twitter and all kinds of platforms.

You haven’t then money for a website.

You haven’t money for stuff like a microphone, pop filter, this and that.

What do you do?

It is the same…

“It is not what you need…but what you already got…….that will take you as far as you want to go…”

So let me give you one final example out of so many in my life.

You will have knowledge in something. Maybe you was a teacher. Maybe you know how to write novels. Maybe you know about children.

Maybe…you’re like me….very good at dating and got the experience, knowledge and the mindset to share such knowledge.

So what I did is I didn’t build a website. Not yet, anyway.

Instead I focused on one platform.

No, not Facebook. Not twitter but a platform where you can share knowledge to a targeted audience that wants to solve this problem.

The social media platform must be knowledge base type where you can share content. If you’re into videos, then use Youtube. If you like writing then see other platforms.

Don’t just join and fall for the hype. Choose just ONE and be consistent. Get to test, see what works, get good at doing your thing.

Be patient. It takes time. You haven’t got thousands of dollars to advertise so you need to be patient and hammer it with focuse.

That’s what I did.

I’d focus on one platform and targeted topics. I’d see the results and test more. Then I’d see more results and I’ll know how leverage such platforms.

I’d move on to other platforms and other mediums and do the same.

That’s when people wanted more than just reading my work. They wanted to hire my expertise because when they applied what I shared, it worked but they had tons of questions. Questions I won’t and really cannot answer on some platforms.

I started to get people who wanted privatre coaching, wanted to learn from me and I made sure they qualified for it. They learnt I was too busy and if they want my time, then pay for that time.

Now guess what I did with the money?

I started investing back into the work. I invested in tools…

I have other microphones coming, mixer, an audio interface and other equipments because along the way, do to this mindset, I learnt to animate, produce music, songs, lyrics, magazines, professional layout books like this..

Combining all my talents together for a vision I have.

EDIT…..
After I posted this answer, here’s what was delivered to my house; drawing tablet…

As you can see, that one thing can change your whole life…

“It’s never about what you need but what you already got.”

Throughout our lives we are told the secret, the success, the whatever is out there but really, it is INSIDE us.

Out there are just resources.

Out there is just lots of different platforms.

Whatever you attract in your life, whether job, career, money, wealth, assets, women, men, opportunities are the FEEDBACK of what you did inside of yourself and the actions we take with what we go.

Life will give us more when we know how to use what we got already. We just need to be resourceful.

If you don’t like the result….then look in the mirror. See the good you got, the things you already have and make them work for you.

Instead of seeing things as a disadvantage, flip it into an advantage.

The one thing that changed my life will change yours.

“It’s never about what you need but what you already got…”

Stop telling yourself you need….

You got the basics. Now make these basics work for you because everytime you look for the quick answer, secret, to get a body fit, to get this or that….you are saying..

“I don’t want to learn the basics. I need a quick fast route”

Look at what you already got and use it.

Have fun with it.

You’ll surprise yourself.

You’ll inspire people around you and people around the world.
